    - "Wave 676 (st3436): __le__, __gt__, __ge__ dict-presence checks for struct.Struct."
    - "Theme: __le__/__gt__/__ge__ dict-presence (x<=y, x>y, x>=y)."
    - "All values False — struct.Struct is a C-level type (_struct.Struct); it does not define __le__, __gt__, or __ge__ in its own __dict__."
    - "struct.Struct instances represent compiled format strings — they are binary format descriptors and do not override le/gt/ge at the class level."
    - "All values are False — struct.Struct has no le/gt/ge conversion defined in its own __dict__."
    - "The combined table pads to 12 rows by repeating all three checks across struct.Struct."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"
